android.bluetooth
Class BluetoothClass.Device

java.lang.Object
  android.bluetooth.BluetoothClass.Device
Enclosing class:
BluetoothClass
public static class BluetoothClass.Device
extends Object

Every Bluetooth device has exactly one device class, comprimised of major and minor components. We have not included the minor classes for major classes: NETWORKING, PERIPHERAL and IMAGING yet because they work a little differently.

Method Detail

getDevice

public static int getDevice(int btClass)
Returns the Device Class component of a bluetooth class. This includes both the major and minor device components. Values returned from this function can be compared with the constants Device.FOO. A bluetooth device can only be associated with one device class.
